# Cross-implementation oracle for DELTA tracking under the shared contract:
# - First occurrence of an RT/MSG key has DELTA = 0.000000.
# - Errored records participate in DELTA tracking (Rust originally
#   hardcoded 0.0, Python computed; the new contract aligns both).
# - Subsequent normal records compute against the prior errored record,
#   and subsequent errored records compute against the prior normal record.
#
# IRIG timestamps. All records target RT15 SA11 Receive (key 15:11R).
# Timestamps: t0=50.000000, t1=50.250000, t2=50.500000 — expected DELTAs are
# 0.000000, 0.250000, 0.250000 respectively.

# Errored RT15 SA11 Receive at 192:15:54:50.000000 (first occurrence of 15:11R).
# TW 0x4702 (type=0x02, Bus A, wc=7, error=1) + IRIG (upper 0x180F, middle 0xDB20, lower 0x0000).
0247 0F18 20DB 0000
7E79 0004 1E01

# Normal RT15 SA11 Receive at 192:15:54:50.250000 — must DELTA against the
# preceding errored record (Rust used to discard the error timestamp).
# TW 0x2402 (type=0x02, Bus A, wc=36, no error) + IRIG (0x180F, 0xDB23, 0xD090).
0224 0F18 23DB 90D0
7E79
0004 0000 0000 2F00 22CA 2F00 22CA
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
71C7 0078

# Errored RT15 SA11 Receive at 192:15:54:50.500000 — must DELTA against the
# preceding normal record (proves the path is symmetric).
# TW 0x4702 + IRIG (0x180F, 0xDB27, 0xA120).
0247 0F18 27DB 20A1
7E79 0004 1E01
